                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1ra">Fols. 1ra-2</locus>ra: Mälkǝʾa Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus "Image of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus", incomplete.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Crudely written in poor hand; the letters are very irregular and angular in shape.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#127vb">Fol. 127vb</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Gäbrä ʾArägawi is mentioned as the purchaser and donor. Other persons mentioned are his father Mäzgäbä Śǝllase and a certain Wälättä Krǝstos. The note is crudely written in strong amaranth over another, erased note in black (in which the names partly remained). The handwriting is similar but not identical to the hand of GMG-017.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#162vb">Fol. 162vb</locus>: Record concerning the commemoration days of the donor's family members (?).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           ʿAmdä Mikaʾel died on 22th Däqsyos (= Taḫśaś). The donor's (?) father died on 5th Yäkkatit and the mother on 8th Mizya[sic].
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#163rb">Fols. 163rb-164</locus>rb: Genealogy (from Žämäl to Wǝddase Maryam [n.l.] Täklat).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The genealogy is written in Amharic and Gǝʿǝz.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Corrections written over erased words and passages, in different hands: e.g., fols. 6vb, 8va, 9rb, 14ra, 22va, 67rb, 69ra, 71ra, 130ra.&#xD;
- Erased notes: fols. 5v, 6r, 7v, 10r, 13v, 17v, 32r, 34r, 96r, 97v, 100ra, 101v, 102r, 105v, 107v, 131v, 132r, 153v, 154rv.&#xD;
- Short supplications for donor Gäbrä ʾArägawi, written interlineally in strong amaranth: fols. 35vb, 42ra, 73ra, 83vb.&#xD;
- Pen trial: fols. 1r, 2r, 164v.&#xD;
- Crude notes, in pen: fols. 1rv, 2rv, 105v, 164v.</item>
                     </list>
